  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Engaging Communities in Border Security and Management in Niger - Phase IV</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project focuses on a long-term national impact on border management by enhancing the cooperation and coordination between rural border communities and the Nigerian authorities responsible for border management to counter trans-border crimes and terrorism in the Tahoua, Maradi and Agadez regions. In doing so, national and local authorities will be prepared to manage migratory and/or humanitarian crisis while ensuring the full respect of human rights for the people on the move.</narrative>
  </description>
